{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_30","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `io.quarkus.gizmo:gizmo2:2.2.0`. Preserved work is available at https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-7022-fails-java-run-io.quarkus.gizmo-gizmo2-2.2.0-d68df304\n\nThe most likely failing stage was the post-generation verification run, not the initial metadata generation. In `logs/io.quarkus.gizmo:gizmo2:2.2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T11-15-40-124592Z.log`, `:nativeTest` fails in `io_quarkus_gizmo.gizmo2.TestClassMakerInnerLoaderTest > rejectsInvalidLocalClassResource()` with `com.oracle.svm.core.jdk.UnsupportedFeatureError: The assertion status of classes is fixed at image build time`, coming from `ClassLoader.setDefaultAssertionStatus(...)` inside `io.quarkus.gizmo2.testing.TestClassMaker.create()`. This points to an unsupported native-image test path rather than missing reachability metadata. A follow-up retry then failed earlier in `logs/io.quarkus.gizmo:gizmo2:2.2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T11-18-12-251216Z.log` with `java.io.IOException: No space left on device` during `:tck-build-logic:compileJava`, which is likely why the workflow ended with `job_failed`.\n\nPlease also inspect `logs/io.quarkus.gizmo:gizmo2:2.2.0/metadata-fix/codex.log` and `logs/io.quarkus.gizmo:gizmo2:2.2.0/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-06-06T11-18-12-966966Z.log`; they record that the intervention removed the unsupported `rejectsInvalidLocalClassResource()` path. The later rerun in `logs/io.quarkus.gizmo:gizmo2:2.2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T11-19-50-536788Z.log` shows the targeted `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.quarkus.gizmo:gizmo2:2.2.0` passing after that intervention.\n\nNext steps:\n1. Review the preserved branch and decide whether removing or rewriting `TestClassMakerInnerLoaderTest.rejectsInvalidLocalClassResource()` is the right permanent fix.\n2. Re-run